Section 1:
1 L.D. 508
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
4 STATE OF MAINE
5 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
6 132ND LEGISLATURE
7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 HOUSE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 226, L.D. 508, “RESOLUTION, Proposing an
9 Amendment to the Constitution of Maine to Require Constitutional Officers to Be Elected
10 by Popular Election”
11 Amend the resolution by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'RESOLUTION, Proposing an Amendment to the Constitution of Maine to Require
13 a Statewide Popular Election of the Secretary of State, the Treasurer of State and the
14 Attorney General Using Ranked-choice Voting'
15 Amend the resolution by striking out all of that part designated "Constitution, Art.
16 V, Pt. Second, §1" (page 1, lines 4 to 8 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
17 'Constitution, Art. V, Pt. Second, §1 is amended to read:
18 Section 1. Election. The Secretary of State shall be chosen biennially at the first
19 session of the Legislature, by joint ballot of the popular election on the same date and in
20 the same manner as provided by this Constitution for the election of Senators and
21 Representatives in convention, except that the votes of all qualified electors must involve
22 in any election involving 3 or more candidates the ranking of candidates in order of
23 preference according to the procedure established by law and the tabulation of such votes
24 must occur in rounds according to the procedure established by law. The Governor shall
25 examine the tabulation and, 7 days before the first Wednesday of December biennially,
26 shall issue a summons to such person as appears to be elected by a majority of all votes
27 returned or, if the electors rank candidates in order of preference, a majority of all votes in
28 the final round of tabulation, to take office.'
29 Amend the resolution by striking out all of that part designated "Constitution, Art.
30 V, Pt. Third, §1" (page 1, lines 15 to 19 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
31 'Constitution, Art. V, Pt. Third, §1 is amended to read:
32 Section 1. Election. The Treasurer shall be chosen biennially, at the first session of
33 the Legislature, by joint ballot of the popular election on the same date and in the same
34 manner as provided by this Constitution for the election of Senators, and Representatives
35 in convention, except that the votes of all qualified electors must involve in any election
36 involving 3 or more candidates the ranking of candidates in order of preference according
37 to the procedure established by law and the tabulation of such votes must occur in rounds
Page 1 - 132LR0721(05)
HOUSE AMENDMENT
HOUSE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 226, L.D. 508
318 according to the procedure established by law. The Governor shall examine the tabulation
329 and, 7 days before the first Wednesday of December biennially, shall issue a summons to
430 such person as appears to be elected by a majority of all votes returned or, if the electors
441 rank candidates in order of preference, a majority of all votes in the final round of
452 tabulation, to take office.'
6 Amend the resolution by striking out all of that part designated "Constitution, Art.
7 IX, §11" (page 1, lines 26 to 32 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
8 'Constitution, Art. IX, §11 is amended to read:
9 Section 11. Attorney General. The Attorney General shall be chosen biennially
10 by joint ballot of the popular election on the same date and in the same manner as provided
11 by this Constitution for the election of Senators and Representatives in convention, except
12 that the votes of all qualified electors must involve in any election involving 3 or more
13 candidates the ranking of candidates in order of preference according to the procedure
14 established by law and the tabulation of such votes must occur in rounds according to the
15 procedure established by law. The Governor shall examine the tabulation and, 7 days
16 before the first Wednesday of December biennially, shall issue a summons to such person
17 as appears to be elected by a majority of all votes returned or, if the electors rank candidates
18 in order of preference, a majority of all votes in the final round of tabulation, to take office.
19 Vacancy in said office occurring when the Legislature is not in session, may be filled by
20 appointment by the Governor, subject to confirmation as required by this Constitution for
21 Justices of the Supreme Judicial Court.'
22 Amend the resolution in the question in the 3rd line (page 2, line 1 in L.D.) by inserting
23 after the following: "manner" the following: ', using ranked-choice voting,'
24 Amend the resolution by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
25 section number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment requires ranked-choice voting to be used for the election of the
2288 Secretary of State, the Treasurer of State and the Attorney General.
2299 SPONSORED BY: ___________________________________
3300 (Representative LEE, A.)
3311 TOWN: Auburn
